<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Fighting game homebrew port demake (w/ video)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11878&amp;p=134689#p134689"><![CDATA[
There was some other game by Namco (Famicom, of course) where you and the enemy shared the same graphics, and you kinda looked like monks.  Then there's the various Culture Brain games with the occasional 1-on-1 perspective, the fighter mode of Double Dragon, and the nefarious Karate Champ.  Fighting games did exist on the NES, but they weren't made in the SF2 era.  That said, I think an SF2 port with graphical assets in the vein of Mighty Final Fight would work spectacularly well, though I'm certain they didn't bother with it because SF2 is defined by it's vocal samples, and Capcom never used samples of any kind in any of their NES games.<br /><br />I wonder if the Chinese would be ambitious enough and port something like Skullgirls to the NES, assuming the game is actually worth bootlegging and if the third world still plays on clone NES consoles.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6132">OneCrudeDude</a> — Mon Oct 06, 2014 5:45 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
